body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Hotel Express customer support. My name is Nathan Henderson. May I please have your name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Ruth Torres.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Ruth. Can you please provide me with the first three digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it is five six seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you. Now, could you share with me the last two digits of your zip code?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, they are nine eight.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Ruth. If there is anything else I can assist you with, please let me know.

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, I think that's all. Thank you for your help.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Ruth. Thank you for reaching out to us. Have a wonderful day.
